stay at home moms isolation i'm a stay at home mom and i love that i have this opportunity to spend my time with my child but sometimes i feel so isolated from the rest of the adult world the problem is compounded by the fact that we live in a rural area where there just aren't a lot of social and entertainment options i find myself wishing i could have just one day when i could get up get dressed go out and do the normal things people do without kids underfoot how do other stay at home moms deal with isolation i got a membership to the ymca i get to go work out every day and have a two hour slot where they watch my kids the kids love this because they get a chance to play with other kids i get to be in shape and have time with adults i love it and they have a program where your rates are dependent on your income so if money is ever a problem they can help with that to The Fairly OddParents Laura Schlessinger Homeschooling Cartoon Network The Adventures of Pete & Pete Slot machine Grief Social rule Transsexuality Labour economics Poker jargon YMCA Microeconomics Economic inequality Autism rights movement KaBlam! Fox Kids Hikikomori Education in the People's Republic of China Treehouse of Horror V Television in the United States Avenue Q About a Boy Hearing impairment Intelligence quotient Little Big Mom Thai royal and noble titles Paracetamol Divorce Undergrads Unemployment Teacher's Pet (Disney) Big Brother UK series 6 Futurama (TV series - season 2) Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder EastEnders Kimi Finster Soap opera Malcolm in the Middle Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Jonestown Charlie and the Chocolate Factory (film) Trailer Park Boys Rent (musical) Hospitality service Ed, Edd n Eddy Narcissism Education in the United States Shaggy dog story Fathers' rights The Brady Bunch Surveillance Current teachings of Prem Rawat Toastmasters International Betting (poker) Culture of the United States Baby Blues Kender Labor theory of value Paragliding Freete